description:
Atomic Alchemy is building a bank of reactors to produce the nuclear material that goes into nuclear medicine. Radiopharmaceuticals are vitally important in biological tracers, diagnostic imaging, and cancer treatments.

Currently, the world's supply of Molybdenum-99, the cornerstone of 80% of all nuclear medicine procedures, is sourced from just six government-run, scientific research reactors abroad. Five of these reactors are 45-65 years old and are quickly coming to the end of their operational life. This has cultivated a fragile and lengthy supply chain, at odds with the nature of radioactive material.

This issue and its implications do not just effect molybdenum, but any other reactor-based isotope. Many promising cancer therapies are stuck in clinical trials, unable to secure enough material in a timely manner. Research doesn’t even happen because of the difficulty of sourcing any new isotopes.

It doesn't have to be this way. Atomic Alchemy is working to solve this by building the world's first scalable radioisotope production facility. This facility will contain the world’s first privately-owned nuclear reactors dedicated to radioisotope production.

description: Dagger is a programmable CI/CD engine that runs your pipelines in containers. Develop your pipelines as code, in the same programming language as your application. Choose your SDK and start coding! Dagger executes your pipelines entirely as standard OCI containers. This has several benefits: - Instant local testing - Portability: the same pipeline can run on your local machine, a CI runner, a dedicated server, or any container hosting service. - Superior caching: every operation is cached by default, and caching works the same everywhere - Compatibility with the Docker ecosystem: if it runs in a container, you can add it to your pipeline. - Cross-language instrumentation: teams can use each other's tools without learning each other's language.
generated_description:
### Dagger: Revolutionizing CI/CD Pipelines

**Overview:**  
Founded in 2018 and a proud member of Y Combinator's Batch W19, Dagger is a forward-thinking company located in San Francisco. With a compact yet effective team of 22 dedicated employees, Dagger is on a mission to transform the way we think about Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment (CI/CD). They aim to empower developers to write their CI/CD pipelines as code, making it easy to run those pipelines anywhere.

**Product Concept:**  
Dagger started as a programmable CI/CD engine, leveraging the power of containers. The revolutionary idea is that you can develop your pipelines using the same programming languages you use for your applications: Go, TypeScript, or Python. This brings a myriad of benefits:

- **Instant Local Testing:** Run your pipelines locally just as you would in production.
- **Portability:** Your pipelines can run anywhere—from your laptop to cloud CI environments.
- **Superior Caching:** Operations are cached automatically, boosting performance, and ensuring consistency across different environments.
- **Docker Compatibility:** If it runs in a container, it seamlessly integrates into your pipeline.
- **Cross-Language Instrumentation:** Teams can utilize each other's tools without needing to dive into unfamiliar languages.

**Core Features:**  
- **API-First Approach:** Dagger champions code over YAML, making complex CI scripts a thing of the past. The focus is on replacing cumbersome scripts with a more intuitive, programmable interface.
- **Standardized Modules:** Users can chain reusable Dagger functions to create efficient pipelines, built by themselves or the community.
- **High Performance:** Advanced caching techniques minimize unnecessary rebuilds and testing, accelerating delivery cycles.
- **Observability:** Gain deep visibility into your pipelines with interactive debugging tools to quickly identify and fix issues.

**Community and Resources:**  
Dagger encourages community involvement where developers can join discussions on platforms like Discord and GitHub. They offer extensive documentation, case studies, and example projects to help newcomers get started seamlessly. 

For those interested:
- **Get Started with Dagger:** [Start Here](https://dagger.io/<https:/docs.dagger.io/quickstart>)
- **Join the Community:** [Join Us](https://dagger.io/<https:/discord.gg/dagger-io>)
- **Learn More:** [Visit Dagger's Website](https://dagger.io)

**Conclusion:**  
Dagger is not just another tool in the CI/CD ecosystem; it stands out by simplifying complexity, enhancing developer experiences, and making pipelines as flexible and powerful as they should be. If your team is looking to eliminate the frustrations of "push & pray" deployments, Dagger is worth a closer look.  

For more detailed insights into its capabilities, check out the testimonials from satisfied users and see how Dagger is changing the game in CI/CD.
headline: Develop your CI/CD pipelines as code and run them anywhere
name: Dagger

### Dockup Overview

Dockup is a proactive solution tailored for engineering teams that need to navigate the complexities of manual and automated testing with confidence. By providing on-demand ephemeral environments, Dockup allows developers to test their code in real-time without the hassle of mock services. It’s akin to what CircleCI offers but with the added benefit of visualizing every code change within the entire tech stack, ensuring that pulls to the main branch are as seamless and reliable as possible.

### Evolution and Mission

Founded in Y Combinator's W19 batch, Dockup started with a clear mission: "On-demand ephemeral environments to run manual and automated tests." Nestled in Mountain View, California, and manned by a dedicated team of just four employees, Dockup has its sights set on simplifying the deployment process. They target developers who are fed up with sifting through convoluted DevOps tutorials and just want a practical solution.

### How Dockup Works

**Setup Process:**
1. Sign up and connect your GitHub and AWS accounts.
2. Dockup autonomously creates the necessary AWS resources for your deployments:
   - **CodeBuild** pulls your source code and builds Docker images.
   - **ECR** stores those images.
   - **EKS** runs them as containers.
   - **IAM** manages user and resource permissions.
   - Network configurations are automatically taken care of with VPCs, subnets, and security groups.

Once set up, deploying code is as easy as pushing to GitHub. You can manage deployment checklists, conduct manual deployments, or perform rollbacks through a user-friendly interface.

### Key Features

- **Free Forever**: Dockup doesn’t lock you in; it utilizes your infrastructure for deployments but can be easily unlinked whenever you need.
- **Auto Scaling and Load Balancing**: The platform dynamically adjusts to traffic patterns, adding or removing nodes as necessary.
- **Rolling Deployments**: Deploy new versions of services incrementally, ensuring zero downtime during updates.
- **SSL Management**: Automatically provisions and renews SSL certificates, taking one more task off your plate.

### Pricing

For teams, Dockup offers an attractive pricing model at $45 monthly, which includes unlimited users, role-based access control, custom deployment checklists, and comprehensive reporting and analytics.

If you're looking to streamline your deployment process with a simple yet powerful tool, Dockup is designed to tackle those challenges head-on, letting you focus on what you do best: building great software.

For more information, check out their website [here](https://getdockup.com/).
headline: On demand ephemeral environments to run manual and automated tests.
name: Dockup

Inito is revolutionizing the way women monitor their reproductive health by enabling at-home hormone tracking. Their mission centers on improving self-care through innovative technology that simplifies fertility management. #### What Makes Inito Unique?

At its core, Inito operates as an all-in-one fertility monitor, measuring four crucial hormones—Estrogen, Luteinizing Hormone (LH), Progesterone (as PdG), and Follicle Stimulating Hormone (FSH)—all on a single test strip. Unlike conventional ovulation tests that typically provide binary “yes/no” results based merely on LH spikes, Inito gives detailed insights into hormone levels, helping women pinpoint their most fertile windows.

In just **10 minutes**, users can dip a test strip in urine, attach it to their smartphone (currently compatible with iPhone 7 and later), and receive personalized, actionable data. This data not only aids in predicting ovulation but also in confirming it, giving users a clearer picture of their fertility cycles. 

#### Why Choose Inito?

- **Comprehensive Hormone Tracking:** Inito is the only fertility monitor that tracks all four hormones simultaneously, providing a more nuanced understanding of menstrual cycles.
- **User-Friendly App:** The accompanying app simplifies the tracking process, sending notifications about test days, results, and confirmed ovulation.
- **Trusted by Couples:** With over 20,000 couples relying on Inito, testimonials highlight successful pregnancies facilitated by accurate hormone monitoring.

#### Key Features:

- **Real-Time Data**: Offers numerical values for hormone levels instead of generic readings, essential for those with irregular cycles.
- **Effective Confirmation**: Helps confirm ovulation through sustained PdG levels, which are critical for successful conception.
- **HSA/FSA Eligible**: This makes it easier for users in the U.S. to afford fertility testing.

#### Frequently Asked Questions:

- **What results does Inito provide?**
  Inito delivers results such as High Fertility, Peak Fertility, and Ovulation Confirmed, along with charts of hormone levels.
  
- **How many test strips are needed per cycle?**
  This varies; an average cycle might require 12-15 tests. 

- **Can I use HSA benefits?**
  Yes, Inito is eligible for HSA purchases.

- **Is it FDA approved?**
  It’s registered as a Class I medical device in the U.S., exempt from many premarket requirements, though it has not been explicitly cleared or approved.

Inito is more than just a product; it’s a tool that empowers women to understand their bodies better and enhance their chances of conception. Whether you’re actively trying to conceive or simply wanting to keep track of your hormonal health, Inito provides an insightful, data-driven approach to fertility monitoring.

For anyone interested in leveraging technology for better reproductive health, Inito is certainly worth considering. Check it out at [Inito.com](https://www.inito.com).

description:
PRONTO is the first RIDE-SHARING + DELIVERY platform for SECOND-TIER cities in LATAM. 

In second-tier cities all transactions are paid with cash, this is why the Uber model doesn´t work (since they have to collect their revenue from commissions). We solved this by creating a subscription model where drivers pay a monthly recurring subscription of 59 to 99 USD depending on their monthly revenue. This also generates a higher LTV with low CAC as well as high engagement and fidelity ratios.

Traction: Since our launch, we have achieved over 2,000,000 processed trips with more than 200,000 users, we bootstrapped until we achieved half a million trips and entered YC.

Market Size: There are over 14,000 second-tier cities in LATAM, with more than 500 million people without any access to ride-sharing or technology platforms at all.

### Company Overview: Pronto

**Mission:** Pronto is revolutionizing ride-sharing and delivery services in second-tier cities across Latin America. Recognizing that cash transactions dominate in these markets, the company has tailored its service to meet local needs in a way that traditional models, like Uber's, can't.

**Business Model:** Unlike typical ride-sharing platforms that charge drivers a percentage of their fares, Pronto operates on a subscription model. Drivers pay a monthly fee ranging from $59 to $99, depending on their revenue. This approach not only alleviates the problem of cash payments but also enhances customer lifetime value (LTV) while keeping customer acquisition costs (CAC) low. The results have been impressive—a loyal driver base and high engagement.

**Traction:** Since its launch, Pronto has facilitated over 2 million trips and amassed more than 200,000 users. After bootstrapping to reach 500,000 trips, Pronto entered Y Combinator in the W19 batch, gaining significant visibility and support.

**Market Opportunity:** There are over 14,000 second-tier cities in Latin America, home to more than 500 million people who currently lack access to reliable ride-sharing and technology platforms. This vast market presents an enormous opportunity for growth.

**Team:** Based in Mexico City, Pronto operates with a team of 62 dedicated employees. Their passion and commitment to improving transportation options in their communities are palpable.

**Future Directions:** Pronto continues to expand both its user base and its service offerings. They aim to create a community-oriented platform where drivers can earn a good income on their own terms—without the burden of commissions.

For more information or to join the Pronto community, check out their [website](http://www.tuprontomx.com/).
headline: Ride-sharing for second-tier cities in Latin America.
name: Pronto

Thrive Agric's mission is simple yet profound: to help farmers in Africa thrive by linking them to essential resources that enable crop growth and maximize profitability. The company aims to ensure food security for all through innovative technology solutions.

4. **Field Monitoring:** Assigning field officers to guide farmers using best practices to ensure successful harvests.
   
5. **Harvesting & Inventory Management:** Facilitating logistics for harvest collection and managing post-harvest inventory to ensure efficient supply chain operations.

- **2,700 communities reached.**

generated_description:
**Ultralight: The Universal, Pure-GPU HTML Renderer**

Founded in 2017 and based in San Francisco, Ultralight is shaking up the world of game and app development with its innovative approach to rendering HTML. As part of the Y Combinator Batch W19, this company has a clear mission: to provide a GPU-accelerated toolkit that makes embedding modern HTML in games and native applications not just feasible, but remarkably efficient. 

### What is Ultralight?

Ultralight is a lightweight fork of WebKit, designed specifically to empower developers using C and C++. Its reach extends across a broad array of platforms— from desktop systems like Windows, macOS, and Linux to gaming consoles like Xbox and PlayStation. The key value proposition? It's fast, lightweight, and portable.

### Why Ultralight Stands Out

1. **Ultra-Fast Rendering**: Ultralight distinguishes itself with a GPU-first architecture that can also utilize CPU rendering. Developers can choose to maximize performance by rendering directly on the GPU, or opt for easy integration with CPU-based rendering, suited for less intense environments.

2. **Ultra-Lightweight Resource Usage**: Ultralight's memory footprint is nearly ten times lighter than that of Chromium. This efficiency allows developers to create applications that consume fewer resources while maintaining strong performance.

3. **Ultra-Portability**: With optimization for various environments— including embedded systems and TVs— Ultralight fits seamlessly into many existing infrastructures. Whether you're developing a game or a desktop application, Ultralight is built to run nearly everywhere.

### Tailored for Game Developers

Ultralight’s development closely collaborates with leading AAA game studios, ensuring that it meets the demanding needs of modern game development. Some standout features include:

- **Deep GPU Integration**: The GPUDriver API allows developers to incorporate accelerated content directly into their existing rendering engines, whether they're using Direct3D, Metal, or OpenGL.

- **Transparent Rendering and Custom Image Compositing**: Rich web content can be rendered transparently over existing in-game visuals, enhancing the integration of HTML within the gaming experience.

### Native App Development Simplified

For native app developers, Ultralight offers straightforward integration with comprehensive support for consistent application performance across operating systems. Features like automatic window management and the ability to call native functions directly from JavaScript bridge the gap between web and native code.

### Trusted by Industry Leaders

Ultralight is already making waves with prominent partners, including major industry players like EA, Square Enix, and Sony, validating its efficacy in real-world applications.

### The Backstory

The team behind Ultralight is no stranger to this domain— they previously crafted Awesomium, the first HTML engine for games. Their journey took a bold turn in 2015 when they decided to move on from Chromium, focusing instead on performance and portability, which culminated in the creation of Ultralight and its private beta launch in 2018.

### Join the Revolution

If you're tired of bloated engines and slow integration processes, it's time to give Ultralight a try. Check out their [website](https://ultralig.ht) to download the SDK, explore the documentation, engage in community discussions on Discord, and see how Ultralight can transform your development experience. 

In a world that's constantly evolving, Ultralight stands as a beacon for developers who want to push the envelope with less overhead and more speed. Don't miss your chance to be part of this innovative movement in HTML rendering.
headline: Universal, Pure-GPU HTML Renderer

generated_description:
**Company Overview: XGenomes**

Founded in 2017 and hailing from Cambridge, MA, XGenomes is revolutionizing the world of genomics with an ambitious mission: to build the sequencing technology of the future. As part of the Y Combinator Batch W19, they've positioned themselves at the cutting edge of DNA sequencing, aiming for a simpler, more affordable, and vastly more accurate solution.

**What They Do**

At its core, XGenomes is creating a novel sequencing platform that integrates biochemistry, hardware, and algorithms into one seamless system. Here’s where they shine:

- **No Library Preparation:** Unlike traditional sequencing methods that require extensive preparation steps, XGenomes sequences directly from unaltered single DNA molecules.
- **Integrated Extraction and Sequencing:** This innovation eliminates time-consuming separate DNA extraction processes.
- **Concurrent Sequencing:** They improve accuracy by sequencing both strands of the DNA double helix at once, providing multiple layers of redundancy.
- **Comprehensive Insights:** The sequences generated capture a complete picture of the genome, covering single nucleotide variants, structural variants, haplotypes, and even the often-ignored repetitive "dark matter" of our DNA.

**Market Impact**

The cost effect is particularly striking: XGenomes projects a cost of goods for sequencing at under $10. This financial strategy positions them well to penetrate the market, aiming for over 90% profit margins while delivering an accessible service. Initially, they plan to operate on a service model for high-value clients before transitioning to a "razor and blade" model, offering instruments and consumables.

**Current Activities and Vision**

XGenomes is not just about technology; their vision extends to making health monitoring a lifelong affair. They leverage artificial intelligence and optical super-resolution imaging to decode molecular interactions, enabling real-time health monitoring, early disease detection, and tracking of individual responses to treatments.

In a world plagued by high error rates, complex workflows, and prohibitive costs of existing genomic technologies, XGenomes steps in with a sleek, user-friendly solution that aims to democratize and streamline genomics for everyone.

**Team and Location**

Currently, XGenomes operates with a lean team of six employees, harnessing expertise and innovation at their Cambridge base, but their ambitions stretch far beyond. They're eyeing expansion and collaboration, potentially to the Bioinnovation Centre at Cambridge Science Park in the UK.

**Final Thoughts**

XGenomes is not just another player in the genomics field; it's a bold bet on the future of health, data, and personalized medicine. As they continue to refine their groundbreaking technology, they stand to redefine our understanding of genetics and its implications for health and longevity. For more on their journey, visit [XGenomes' website](http://www.xgenomes.com).
headline: XGenomes is building the sequencing technology of the future.
